My main gripe with this is the lack of pogo pins. I have an original N7, and the dock, and I love being able to use it as a digital picture frame when I'm not actively using it (and having it still be fully charged when I grab it). The lack of pogo pins/first-party docking solution is very disappointing to me. I might still get one just because of how slow the IO is on the original. (And the slowness of the IO on the original has a noticeable impact on user experience, not just 'oh, copying movies to it is slow'.)
