Posted: Wed Jul 31, 2013 8:02 am
thegeneral wrote:Or to compare a 7" Nexus to the 7.85" iPad-Mini which has 40% more physical screen space.Wait, wha? A 1920x1200 vs 1024x768 is a 2.9 difference in pixel count, that's close to Retina's 4x difference in pixel. So I guess Retina is just a "greater-than-slightly higher resolution" compared to non-Retina.thegeneral wrote:Sure the Nexus has slightly higher resolution but just makes everything even smaller to read.No they won't. Android OS takes DPI into account when rendering so it will render texts to the same physical size. The same app on 2012 N7 will have the same physical size on 2013 N7.
