shompa
Smack-Fu Master, in training
Registered: Sep 5, 2012Posts: 65
Posted: Wed Jul 31, 2013 8:09 am
Can I "trust" this review?Remember last year how all reviewers praised the Nexus7. Today nobody uses it and reviewers calls the original Nexus7 junk. Will history repeat itself? BTW: Performance can't be measured by benchmarks when you compare a integrated eco system against a fragmented. The companies that control their OS and Hardware can optimise program. For example the A5: 30% of the die area is for Apple specific stuff like NOVA SIMD, sound DSPs for Siri and a fast memory controller. An optimised SIMD program will always be faster then a brute force "PC thinking" Android.Just look at game consoles. The platform exclusive titles are always better since they can be optimised. Supporting many platforms forces you to develop to the lowest common point. This is one of the main reasons why Apple EOL working macs/iOS devises to make the lowest entry point higher for developers. And I don't "hate Google". I will probably buy Nexus7 to get an Android device how Google invisions it.
