I've had mine for 4 days now, and found it to be very nice. The only problem I have run in to has been reading comics in the Dark Horse app, but even that has not been a terribly bothersome experience.I have a couple caces to try on order, and plan to get a Qi charge this afternoon on the way home.araemo wrote:My main gripe with this is the lack of pogo pins. I have an original N7, and the dock, and I love being able to use it as a digital picture frame when I'm not actively using it (and having it still be fully charged when I grab it). The lack of pogo pins/first-party docking solution is very disappointing to me. I might still get one just because of how slow the IO is on the original. (And the slowness of the IO on the original has a noticeable impact on user experience, not just 'oh, copying movies to it is slow'.)I will point out, regarding charging, that it does have wireless Qi. It's an additional cost if you already own a pogo dock, unfortunately, but Qi chargers are almost trivially cheap; you can walk in to a Verizon store and get one for $40. Amazon, etc, are $5 or so cheaper.I'm thinking about ripping out my touchstone mod on my Galaxy Nexus and replicating it with a Qi mod, if the voltages look right.
