I bought the original Nexus 7 very reluctantly because of its lack of expandable SD memory. I am almost ashamed to admit that I haven't really missed it. There are so many ways to get a data and media stored on LAN devices that I don't think I'll ever buy an SD card again.On the other hand, over the past year, the thing has slowed to a crawl... Also the display on the original is very desaturated. Overall, am not terribly pleased with it and not exactly excited to give them more money.
