Mark Havel wrote:Except for the entertaining sight of people looking ridiculous while taking photos with tablets, what's the point of having a rear-facing camera in those devices, especially if it's "middling at best"?It's for taking photographs ~ not sure if people care what they look like doing it, or why they would.If you work in an autoshop or in auto insurance and use a tablet, you use the rear-facing camera to take pics of the damage. If you're a field agent, you use the camera at sights, having one less thing to bring with you when surveying. If you're a chef preparing a menu, you probably use the camera to take pics of the day's dishes. I can think of tons of examples.I can't imagine why a tablet wouldn't have a rear-facing camera on it and be anywhere as useful for many people.
